                <Class>
                    <__p_name>AbstractWriter</__p_name>
                    <__p_description>This is the abstract writer class. A writer is a process interface that writes new output of a source code file. Writers can create additional writers as children whose output is also added to the source code file output, after the parent writer's header and before its footer. This allows modular object oriented design where each writer can be responsible for a specific type of code output. All children writers must be added in the parent's initialization method.

A method for looking up readers in all writer's shared parent parser is provided to allow writers the ability to take scanned code lines.</__p_description>
                    <__p_parents>ABC</__p_parents>
                    <__p_infile>0</__p_infile>
                    <Function>
                        <__p_name>__init__</__p_name>
                        <__p_description>Initializes this new abstract writer with the given parent.</__p_description>
                        <__p_static>0</__p_static>
                        <__p_class>0</__p_class>
                        <__p_abstract>0</__p_abstract>
                        <Object>
                            <__p_name>parent</__p_name>
                            <__p_description>object
The parent of this new abstract writer. If this is a root writer then the parent must be the parser that created it, else the parent must be the parent writer that created this new child writer.</__p_description>
                        </Object>
                    </Function>
                    <Function>
                        <__p_name>__call__</__p_name>
                        <__p_description>Getter method.</__p_description>
                        <__p_returnsDescription>result
lines
Output code lines written to this writer's source code file. If this is a root writer then this is the full code output, else if this is a child it is a code fragment added after its parent's header and before its footer.</__p_returnsDescription>
