                        <__p_name>key</__p_name>
                        <__p_description>Getter method.

Because a module reader exists for the dummy container module for each class, keys must adjust to this fact. The given module flag must be true if a module writer is calling this method or false otherwise. In this way the class name is correctly used only once for the dummy module writer to find its dummy module reader. In all other instances of this being the class, nested class, or function writer the root class name is correctly appended twice in order for the writer to find its reader.</__p_description>
                        <__p_returnsDescription>result
string
