                        </Function>
                        <Function>
                            <__p_name>__scan_</__p_name>
                            <__p_description>Recursively scans the given input file for code of function definitions enclosed in the given namespace scope. Any scanned code of function definitions are added to this parser's definitions dictionary.</__p_description>
                            <__p_static>0</__p_static>
                            <__p_class>0</__p_class>
                            <__p_abstract>0</__p_abstract>
                            <Object>
                                <__p_name>ifile</__p_name>
                                <__p_description>io.TextIOWrapper
The input file that is scanned for function definition code.</__p_description>
                            </Object>
                            <Object>
                                <__p_name>scope</__p_name>
                                <__p_description>string
The namespace scope that any found function definitions are nested within.</__p_description>
                            </Object>
                        </Function>
                        <Function>
                            <__p_name>__scanArgument_</__p_name>
                            <__p_description>Getter method.</__p_description>
                            <__p_returnsDescription>string
The argument signature of the given argument line. The signature removes any spaces and the name of the argument, leaving only the type. This only works with arguments where the last word is the variable name separated from its type, including asterisks or ampersands. This also works with C style function pointers.</__p_returnsDescription>
                            <__p_static>0</__p_static>
                            <__p_class>0</__p_class>
                            <__p_abstract>0</__p_abstract>
                            <Object>
                                <__p_name>line</__p_name>
                                <__p_description>string
A function argument whose signature is returned.</__p_description>
                            </Object>
                        </Function>
                        <Function>
                            <__p_name>__scanFunction_</__p_name>
                            <__p_description>Getter method.</__p_description>
                            <__p_returnsDescription>list
Code lines scanned from the given input file, assuming it is at the beginning of a function definition. It stops scanning lines when the final enclosing bracket is found. The line with the last ending bracket is not included with the returned lines.</__p_returnsDescription>
                            <__p_static>0</__p_static>
                            <__p_class>0</__p_class>
                            <__p_abstract>0</__p_abstract>
                            <Object>
                                <__p_name>ifile</__p_name>
                                <__p_description>io.TextIOWrapper
The input file positioned at the beginning of a function definition whose lines of code are scanned and returned.</__p_description>
                            </Object>
                        </Function>
                        <Function>
                            <__p_name>__scanHeader_</__p_name>
                            <__p_description>Getter method.</__p_description>
                            <__p_returnsDescription>list
Preprocessor header lines scanned from the given input file, assuming it is at the beginning of the file. This will include the header guard lines if the given input file is a C++ header.</__p_returnsDescription>
                            <__p_static>0</__p_static>
                            <__p_class>0</__p_class>
                            <__p_abstract>0</__p_abstract>
                            <Object>
                                <__p_name>ifile</__p_name>
                                <__p_description>io.TextIOWrapper
The input file positioned at the beginning of the file whose preprocessor header lines are scanned and returned.</__p_description>
                            </Object>
                        </Function>
                        <Function>
                            <__p_name>__scanSignature_</__p_name>
                            <__p_description>Getter method.</__p_description>
                            <__p_returnsDescription>string
The function signature scanned from the given input file, assuming it is positioned at the line after the first declaration line. The given function name and ending is used to generate the signature taken from the first declaration line. The returned signature does not include any scope.</__p_returnsDescription>
                            <__p_static>0</__p_static>
                            <__p_class>0</__p_class>
                            <__p_abstract>0</__p_abstract>
                            <Object>
                                <__p_name>ifile</__p_name>
                                <__p_description>io.TextIOWrapper
The input file positioned after the first declaration line of a function header whose signature is scanned and returned.</__p_description>
                            </Object>
                            <Object>
                                <__p_name>name</__p_name>
                                <__p_description>string
The function name of the returned signature.</__p_description>
                            </Object>
                            <Object>
                                <__p_name>end</__p_name>
                                <__p_description>string
The ending of the first function declaration line of the returned signature, used for functions that have no arguments.</__p_description>
                            </Object>
                        </Function>
